<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1239,2022]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1563,1590]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Comments.</emphasis>
In some genera of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" box="[556,724,1563,1589]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Batrachideinae">Batrachideinae</taxonomicName>
and other genera of other subfamilies, limits are not clear, and it is usual that species in closely-related genera have been placed here, but they clearly not belong when reviewed more closely. This was the case, for instance, when 
<bibRefCitation author="Hancock, J. L." box="[722,905,1635,1662]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="387 - 426" refId="ref31709" refString="Hancock, J. L. (1909 [1908]) Further studies of the Tetriginae (Orthoptera) in the Oxford University Museum. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, 56 (3 - 4), 387 - 426. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1909. tb 02160. x" type="journal article" year="1909">Hancock (1909)</bibRefCitation>
, descry 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1909" box="[995,1141,1635,1662]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis box="[995,1141,1635,1662]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Scaria brevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a male specimen from Cachabi, 
<collectingCountry box="[317,410,1671,1697]" name="Ecuador" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[425,597,1671,1698]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1856,1881]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,409,1748]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,409,1836]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 6. Scaria brevis Hancock 1909 type (=Batrachidea brevis comb. nov.) A. Habitus in lateral view and labels. B. Habitus in dorsal view. (Photos: Hope Entomological Collections)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3467990" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3467990/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 6A and 6B</figureCitation>
); and then 
<bibRefCitation author="Hebard, M." box="[719,882,1671,1698]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="165 - 313" refId="ref31865" refString="Hebard, M. (1923) Studies in the Dermaptera and Orthoptera of Colombia. Third paper. Orthopterous family Acrididae. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 49, 165 - 313." type="journal article" year="1923">Hebard (1923)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1923" box="[1002,1231,1671,1697]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Batrachidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inermis">
<emphasis box="[1002,1231,1671,1697]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Batrachidea inermis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a female specimen (
<figureCitation box="[274,451,1707,1734]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1744,1769]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,265,1725]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,265,1725]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 7. Batrachidea inermis Hebard, 1923 syn. nov. Type (=Batrachidea brevis comb. nov.) A. Habitus in lateral view and. B. dorsal view respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3467994" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3467994/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 7A and 7B</figureCitation>
) from Andagoya, 
<collectingRegion box="[658,773,1707,1733]" country="Colombia" name="Antioquia" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Antioquia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[786,896,1707,1733]" name="Colombia" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(currently this location is within the borders of 
<collectingRegion box="[151,363,1743,1770]" country="Colombia" name="Choco" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Chocó department</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1239,2022]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
In all specimens reviewed of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" box="[646,719,1780,1806]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[646,719,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Scaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
no brachypronotal form was ever found, so we consider that in this genus, only macropronotal forms exist. On the other hand, in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1838" box="[908,1046,1815,1841]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Batrachidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[908,1046,1815,1841]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Batrachidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is usual to find both macro and brachypronotal forms (sometimes in the same location along each other), which can give rise to confusions, as the macropronotal forms of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1838" box="[425,563,1887,1913]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Batrachidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[425,563,1887,1913]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Batrachidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, can superficially resemble 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" box="[879,952,1888,1914]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[879,952,1888,1914]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Scaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the brachypronotal ones could be mistaken for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grant" authorityYear="1956" box="[258,379,1923,1949]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Rehnidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[258,379,1923,1949]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Rehnidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1239,2022]" lastBlockId="16.[151,1436,153,396]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
As for 
<bibRefCitation author="Hebard, M." box="[278,444,1959,1986]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="165 - 313" refId="ref31865" refString="Hebard, M. (1923) Studies in the Dermaptera and Orthoptera of Colombia. Third paper. Orthopterous family Acrididae. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 49, 165 - 313." type="journal article" year="1923">Hebard (1923)</bibRefCitation>
, females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1909" box="[582,678,1959,1986]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis box="[582,678,1959,1986]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">S. brevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were unknown, he described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1923" box="[1015,1131,1960,1985]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Batrachidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inermis">
<emphasis box="[1015,1131,1960,1985]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">B. inermis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with females, but males of the same locality he unknowingly determined as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1909" box="[711,808,1995,2022]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis box="[711,808,1995,2022]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">S. brevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, not realizing that they are the same species. In 
<emphasis italics="true" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Batra- chidea</emphasis>
males and females are quite different from each other and it is often necessary to collect two in order to be certain of the association, unlike 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" box="[525,598,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[525,598,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Scaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
where males and females are very much alike. Hebard’s confusion spread up to the contributions of 
<bibRefCitation author="Grant Jr., H. J." box="[447,600,224,251]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="67 - 108" refId="ref31328" refString="Grant Jr., H. J. (1956 a) The taxonomy of Batrachidea, Puiggaria, Lophoscirtus, Eutettigidea and Rehnidium n. gen. (Orthotpera: Acridoidea, Tetrigidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 82, 67 - 108." type="journal article" year="1956">Grant (1956a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Grant, H. J." box="[612,672,225,252]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refId="ref31464" refString="Grant, H. J. (1962) A revision of the subfamily Batrachideinae (Orthoptera; Tetrigidae). PhD Thesis, University of Colorado Library, University of Colorado, Colorado, 208 pp." type="book" year="1962">1962</bibRefCitation>
), who notes that the males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1923" box="[1014,1130,226,251]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Batrachidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inermis">
<emphasis box="[1014,1130,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">B. inermis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remained unknown, but in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" box="[193,266,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[193,266,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Scaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
section of his thesis, he redescribes 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1909" box="[674,769,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Scaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis box="[674,769,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">S. brevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mentioning also the lack of female specimens and adds the record of two additional males, one from, Muzo, 
<collectingRegion box="[704,791,297,323]" country="Colombia" name="Boyaca" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Boyacá</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[803,916,297,323]" name="Colombia" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, and other from Tingo Maria, 
<collectingCountry box="[1255,1310,297,323]" name="Peru" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Peru</collectingCountry>
. It is worth mentioning that in Muzo and surrounding locales the only species of the family is 
<taxonomicName authority="Bolivar, 1887" authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Batrachidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavonotata">
<emphasis box="[1067,1340,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Batrachidea flavonotata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bolivar, I." pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="175 - 313" refId="ref30415" refString="Bolivar, I. (1887) Essai sur les Acridiens de la tribu des Tettigidae. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique, 31, 175 - 313." type="journal article" year="1887">Bolívar, 1887</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(as per field observations and collecting efforts by O. J. Cadena-Castañeda).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3467990" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3467990" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3467990/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" startId="16.[151,250,1856,1881]" targetBox="[151,1433,409,1748]" targetPageId="16">
